@ENDNODE

@NODE "Tips & Tricks für Spieler" "Tips & Tricks für Spieler"

@{b}PLAYER-HINTS@{ub}

@{b}1.General@{ub}

Of cause, these can't be univeral hints. You might find yourself confronted
by a small slimy frog, but you might even be a balrog's victim!

All,  who  don't  want  to  play  'hack&slash'  should  read  the following
instructions carefuly!


@{b}terrain@{ub}

Try  to  attack from higher fields.  These charges get a bonus.  Don't come
to  a  stand  where you can't fall back, for a stronger opponent might push
you  back.   If  you can't fall back, you will suffer bad damages.  You may
also  use  this  strategy  for your own attacks (select push away).  If you
don't  play a water-creature, stay off the water!  You might drown and your
attacks even get a malus.


@{b}setup@{ub}

Bowmen  may  fire  directly  over  their  frontmen  without  a danger.  But
standing  elsewhere in the line of fire might be harmful (depending on your
size).

Try  to  get a good view, so that you, or at last all players together, are
able to watch the whole scene.  You might miss some details!

@{b}kinetic energy@{ub}

Crushing  into  the  enemy with speed gives you an additional bonus on your
attack.   But pray to the Gods if your opponent is able to strike back, for
your defensive-value gets a malus!

@{b}special actions@{ub}

Don't  attack  each  round.   Try  to hide or sneak to your target.  Aim or
concentrate, if you are not involved in close-combat.

@{b}how to attack@{ub}

You   might   detect,   that   you're   charging   early   or  late  during
combat-sequence.   That  depends  on your maneuver-value.  So keep in mind,
that  others  might  strike first, or strike back --- combine attacks.  The
late  attacks  will  cause  seriouse  damage, for the defensive-values gets
decremented by each attack. Don't get surrounded!

Don't strike on all, if many might strike back --- you will decrement their
devensive-value, but your defensive-value will be low, too!

If you're strong enough, try to push your opponent out of the way!

@{b}into the unknown@{ub}

Even 'stupid' npcs will try to prepare their bows.  So running alone around
a  corner  might be like an execution (if three or more archers wait on the
other side!).

@ENDNODE

